==English==

===Etymology===
From {{m|en|four}} + {{m|en|score|t=a grouping of 20}} + {{m|en|and}} + {{m|en|seven}} + {{m|en|years}} + {{m|en|ago}}, literally “87 years ago”, the beginning of the {{w|Gettysburg Address}} made on November 19, 1863, by [[w:President of the United States|United States President]] {{w|Abraham Lincoln}} (1809–1865). The widespread familiarity of Lincoln’s address, the unusual and poetic wording, and its status as the first words of the speech have caused the phrase to enter the public consciousness.

